  "riddle": "1. Begin your journey at the heart of a tranquil subdistrict within Chiang Mai Province in Thailand — Ping Khong. Your quest is to discover how many individuals resided here in 2020.\n\n2. From this traditional enclave, expand your view to the land of smiles. For this entire kingdom, seek the number of its people, as offered by the world’s census.\n\n3. Journey next to an island steeped in history, known for its legendary Colossus, where the highest point is known by the name Attavyros. What's the elevation that this Greek pinnacle reaches?\n\n4. Once you’ve scaled the heights of clue 3, transform that elevation by counting how many letters its Roman numeral expression demands.\n\n5. Now, traverse the European landscapes to a Scandinavian nation of vast forests and lakes. Pinpoint how high above the sea level its capital sits.\n\n6. Switch your focus to a global institution representing faith for well over a billion souls. What was the estimated number of their flock as recorded in 2019?\n\n7. Navigate to the remains of a great repository of human knowledge, once in the Egyptian city by the sea. What year was this beacon of learning established?\n\n8. Among the echoes of ancient scrolls, measure how high this historic library sits above the Mediterranean waves.\n\n9. Within proximity to this place of learning, count the culinary homes where travelers and locals alike gather to nourish their bodies.\n\n10. Take these latest measures — the library's height atop its elevation plus the number of local eateries — and find their sum.\n\n11. Return to the year you unearthed in the library's founding and engage with its prime factors. What is the sum of all the distinct ones?\n\n12. To uncover your final answer, reckon the values stemming from clues 4, 7, and 10. Calculate the absolute difference between the results of clue 4 and the value from clue 7, and find its remainder when divided by 10. This final numeric answer will serve as the key to this quest.",
